{
    "name": "Giant Mosquito",
    "type": "creature",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Giant Mosquito",
            "type": "section",
            "text": "These horrifically enlarged versions of the common mosquito often prey upon megafauna like dinosaurs and other large creatures, but they won't turn down a chance to drink the blood of a smaller target\u2014such as a humanoid.",
            "sources": [
                {
                    "type": "source",
                    "name": "Monster Core 2",
                    "link": {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Monster Core 2 pg. 228",
                        "alt": "Monster Core 2 pg. 228",
                        "game-obj": "Sources",
                        "aonid": 276
                    },
                    "page": 228
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Mosquito",
            "type": "section",
            "sections": [
                {
                    "name": "Malaria Strains",
                    "type": "section",
                    "text": "The most common version of malaria\u2014a pernicious disease often associated with mosquitoes\u2014is presented within GM Core, and while the variants inflicted by mosquito swarms and giant mosquitoes are deadlier, they don\u2019t have the chance to recur after 1d4 months. Pyrexic malaria also causes weakness and fevers, while septic malaria causes painful and infected lesions to form on the body. Regardless of the strain you contract, you can\u2019t reduce your sickened condition while you\u2019re affected with malaria.",
                    "sources": [
                        {
                            "type": "source",
                            "name": "Monster Core 2",
                            "link": {
                                "type": "link",
                                "name": "Monster Core 2 pg. 228",
                                "alt": "Monster Core 2 pg. 228",
                                "game-obj": "Sources",
                                "aonid": 276
                            },
                            "page": 228
                        }
                    ],
                    "subtype": "sidebar",
                    "sidebar_type": "advice_and_rules",
                    "sidebar_heading": "Advice and Rules",
                    "image": {
                        "type": "image",
                        "name": "Advice and Rules",
                        "image": "Sidebar_1_AdviceAndRules.png"
                    },
                    "links": [
                        {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "malaria",
                            "alt": "malaria",
                            "game-obj": "Diseases",
                            "aonid": 30
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "GM Core",
                            "alt": "GM Core",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 218
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ],
            "text": "While the common mosquito is a pest capable of spreading deadly diseases, their giant kin and ravenous clouds of mosquito swarms are even more dangerous.",
            "sources": [
                {
                    "type": "source",
                    "name": "Monster Core 2",
                    "link": {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Monster Core 2 pg. 228",
                        "alt": "Monster Core 2 pg. 228",
                        "game-obj": "Sources",
                        "aonid": 276
                    },
                    "page": 228
                }
            ]
        }
    ],
